{"type":"message","id":"d0b9b43a","parentId":"079d2716","timestamp":"2026-03-26T16:28:28.680Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"web_fetch only got the footer (legal text), no actual search results. The actual content is loaded dynamically via JavaScript, which web_fetch can't handle. I need to use the browser with the correct profile to access the logged-in session.\n\nThe issue is: the browser opened with the default profile which has the Chrome not running error for `profile=\"user\"`. But the second attempt without specifying profile worked (targetId returned). However, that browser session is showing the login page because it's not logged in to 小红书.\n\nLet me try the Chrome Relay approach (profile=\"chrome-relay\") since the user might have the extension installed and can click the toolbar button. Or I need to ask the user if they can log in to 小红书 in the browser.\n \nI'm realizing the core blocker: 小红书 requires authentication to view content, and the MCP search tool doesn't return direct URLs, just note IDs. The browser is showing a login page even though the extension might have the session cookies. Let me try the chrome-relay profile since it explicitly handles the extension relay flow, which might have the authentication state I need. that badge ON).\n\nBut the user would need to click the toolbar button first. Maybe I should explain the situation clearly:\n\n1. The post exists (found via MCP search)\n2. To get the URL, I need to access the logged-in browser session\n3. The browser opened in an isolated profile which isn't logged in to 小红书\n4. Options: a) user logs in via the browser, b) user clicks Chrome extension relay, or c) I try chrome-relay profile\n\nActually, let me just try the chrome-relay profile. The user may have the extension installed and can click it.\n\nBut actually - the simplest thing here is to just give the user what I know. The post title is \"全网统计：英雄联盟当前版本皮肤top100\" by 作者：游戏君. Without a direct URL from the search tool, I can't construct the xiaohongshu URL without the note ID. Let me see if there's another way to get the note ID or URL from the MCP search.\n\nActually, let me try the MediaCrawler MCP approach since it's already deployed and has login states cached. The MCP search tool returned results, so maybe it has more data available. If I can make a direct request to the MediaCrawler endpoint at localhost:18080, I could get the actual URLs for these posts."},{"type":"text","text":"浏览器被小红书拦截了（需要登录）。我换用已部署的MediaCrawler MCP来拿链接：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e4ukm6qs4biv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport requests, json, time\n\n# 1. 连接 SSE 获取 session_id\nr = requests.get('http://127.0.0.1:18080/sse', stream=True, timeout=10)\nendpoint = None\nfor line in r.iter_lines():\n    line = line.decode()\n    if line.startswith('data:'):\n        endpoint = line[5:].strip()\n        break\nr.close()\nprint('endpoint:', endpoint)\n\n# 2. 搜索\nresp = requests.post(f'http://127.0.0.1:18080{endpoint}', json={\n    'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'id': 1, 'method': 'tools/call',\n    'params': {'name': 'crawl_search', 'arguments': {\n        'platform': 'xhs',\n        'store_type': 'json',\n        'keywords': '英雄联盟皮肤top100'\n    }}\n}, timeout=30)\nprint(resp.text[:3000])\n\"","yieldMs":25000,"timeout":35}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774542491516}}
