{"type":"message","id":"adc1cd44","parentId":"5f512445","timestamp":"2026-03-26T17:28:00.480Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The MediaCrawler is running but the browser is just showing \"Error\" in the console - likely the page is showing a login QR code or similar. The browser needs the user to scan the QR code to log in.\n\nLooking at the log, it says `chrome-extension://hmeohemhimcjlegdjloglnkfablbneif/inject.bundle.js` - this is the小红书 browser extension injecting something. And there are many \"Error\" messages which likely mean the browser automation is hitting some issues.\n\nThe problem is that MediaCrawler needs to be logged in. Let me check if there's stored login data that works.\n\nActually, the chrome_debug.log shows the browser is running and hitting the 小红书 page. \n\nThe \"Error\" messages suggest the page content can't be accessed - likely a login barrier blocking the automation. I should check if the browser data directory contains valid login credentials that would let me bypass this."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ji8bqcf6tr8k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\ADHD_agent\\media-crawler-mcp\\browser_data\\xhs_user_data_dir\\Default\\Local Storage\\leveldb\" | Select-Object Name, Length","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774546074464}}
