{"type":"message","id":"cfaa6c96","parentId":"ac07c81b","timestamp":"2026-03-26T17:28:14.238Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The browser is getting \"Error\" from the page - likely a login issue or CAPTCHA. The MediaCrawler MCP is running but can't scrape because it needs login cookies. The cookies in the browser data are probably stale or the account needs re-authentication.\n\nLet me think about what else I can try:1. The小红书 MCP (port 18060, Docker) - this has its own login state separate from MediaCrawler2. It was working before (it listed feeds earlier)3. The issue was that it doesn't have a search function\n\nWait - I did get results from the小红书 MCP earlier when I called `search_notes`! The error was \"unknown tool `search_notes`\" but that was from the wrong MCP. \n\nI should go back to the Docker MCP running on port 18060 - that's what actually worked when I called `list_feeds`, and the feed data had proper encoding like `displayTitle` fields, so it was returning real content. The Docker container has been running for 3 days, so its authentication might still be valid.\n\nThe issue is that `list_feeds` just gives me the homepage, not search results. But wait - I did get actual search results earlier when I ran search_notes against port 18060, and those results included note IDs and metadata like likedCount and displayTitle. That error about \"unknown tool\" might have been a timeout issue rather than a real problem with the tool itself. Let me try calling search_notes again with better timeout handling."},{"type":"text","text":"小红书 MCP Docker 容器之前是通的，再试一次搜索接口：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_74i8oq96o7kr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport requests, json, time\n\ns = requests.Session()\nhdrs = {'Accept':'application/json, text/event-stream'}\nr1 = s.post('http://localhost:18060/mcp', json={'jsonrpc':'2.0','id':1,'method':'initialize','params':{'protocolVersion':'2024-11-05','capabilities':{},'clientInfo':{'name':'openclaw','version':'1.0'}}}, headers=hdrs, timeout=20)\nprint('session_id:', r1.headers.get('Mcp-Session-Id', ''))\nhdrs['Mcp-Session-Id'] = r1.headers.get('Mcp-Session-Id', '')\ns.post('http://localhost:18060/mcp', json={'jsonrpc':'2.0','method':'notifications/initialized'}, headers=hdrs, timeout=10)\n\n# Try search_notes\ntry:\n    resp = s.post('http://localhost:18060/mcp', json={'jsonrpc':'2.0','id':2,'method':'tools/call','params':{'name':'search_notes','arguments':{'keyword':'英雄联盟皮肤top100','limit':5}}}, headers=hdrs, timeout=30)\n    print(resp.text[:3000])\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('Error:', e)\n\"","yieldMs":28000,"timeout":35}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774546080928}}
