{"type":"message","id":"6f31d276","parentId":"a59ba61b","timestamp":"2026-03-26T18:21:23.585Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MediaCrawler is waiting for QR code scan! It's trying to log in to Xiaohongshu via QR code. This means it needs a fresh login. Let me check if it has cached cookies from a previous session. The browser data directory has cookies, but the login is failing because the cookies are expired/invalid.\n\nLooking at the log: \"Ping xhs failed\" → \"try to login again\" → \"waiting for scan code login\"\n\nThis means every time we start MediaCrawler, it needs to scan a QR code to log in. There's no cached valid session.\n\nThe issue is that I can't see the QR code - it's a headless browser. Let me check if there's a way to see the QR code image, or if we can use the existing xiaohongshu-mcp Docker container which might already have valid cookies.\n\n\nThe Docker container was up for 3 days but the search tool wasn't available, so maybe the cookies are session-based and have expired. Let me try checking if the MCP server itself is still responsive rather than trying to restart the container."},{"type":"text","text":"MediaCrawler 在等扫码登录——浏览器里小红书登录态过期了。看看 Docker 容器里的小红书 MCP 有没有缓存的登录状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oy94x00y29su_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec xiaohongshu-mcp ls /app/","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774549276393}}
