{"type":"message","id":"e7c5845a","parentId":"42b3d0b0","timestamp":"2026-03-26T18:21:40.607Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The xiaohongshu-mcp Docker container doesn't have a search_notes tool either. It only has the tools I listed earlier. The search_notes tool was something I was hoping for but it doesn't exist.\n\nWait - let me look more carefully. From the tool list, there was NO search tool. Only: check_login_status, delete_cookies, favorite_feed, get_feed_detail, get_login_qrcode, like_feed, list_feeds, post_comment_to_feed.\n\nSo the Docker MCP for 小红书 doesn't have search capability. Only the browser-based MediaCrawler has that, which requires login.\n\nLet me check if there's another approach - maybe the 小红书 MCP can use the search page through its internal browser context (list_feeds uses the home page)?\n\n\nThe MediaCrawler is waiting for a QR code scan on the local browser, but there's no display attached, so the user can't scan it. The Docker container has a get_login_qrcode tool that returns a Base64 QR code image - if I can retrieve that and display it to the user in Feishu, they could scan it to authenticate.\n\nBut the Docker container's tools don't actually include search_notes, so that's not the issue here. The real problem is that I'm trying to search without authentication. I need to explain this limitation to the user clearly."},{"type":"text","text":"Docker 容器里的小红书 MCP **根本没有搜索功能**，只有首页推送。\n\nMediaCrawler 有搜索但登录态过期了，在等扫码。\n\n**现状：**\n- Docker 容器的小红书 MCP → 没有搜索工具\n- MediaCrawler → 搜索需要扫码登录，之前扫过一次但过期了\n\n**解决：你帮我重新扫一下码就行。**\n\n我拿到 MediaCrawler 的二维码发给你，你小红书扫一下，登录成功就能搜了。要试试吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774549291922}}
